OL,3,C1 in 5 Welsh pensioners left without
OL,4,Cheating at some point this winter
OL,6,FThe figures come as concern grows of a
OL,7,Flooming pensioner poverty time bomb in
OL,8,FWales, which has the UK's oldest
OL,9,Fpopulation.
OL,11,FAfter decades of progress in reducing
OL,12,Fthe rate of among pensioners, that
OL,13,Ftrend is being reversed. In 1994,
OL,14,Fnearly three in ten over-65s lived in
OL,15,Fpoverty, but by 2012 the rate had
OL,16,Fplummeted to just 13% - the lowest
OL,17,Frate for any group.
OL,19,FHowever, it has been steadily climbing
OL,20,Ffor eight years, reaching 18%.
