OL,6,FWe visited two businesses and a
OL,7,Fcharity who told us they have had to
OL,8,Fstep in to help struggling pensioners
OL,9,Fat cost, as services which used to be
OL,10,Frun by have been cut.
OL,12,F"People are turning off their lights,
OL,13,Fwe've got people that come here that
OL,14,Fonly have a shower once a week because
OL,15,Fof the cost of water," said Sarah
OL,16,FMason, who runs Helping Our Homeless
OL,17,FWales.
OL,19,FShe said more and more elderly people
OL,20,Fare relying on warm spaces like her
OL,21,Fcentre in Builth Wells, , to survive.
